      "role": "user",
      "content": "<thought\n>Being \"real\" and \"owning shame\" still feels like such a heavy weight though. I see the look in their eyes sometimes, like they're just absorbing my stress and my mess. It's like I'm a poison in the house. I just want them to have a life that isn't defined by my constant struggle. I feel like the only way they ever get a real chance to be happy is if I just wasn't a constant shadow over them.",
